headline: DoorDash stock tanks after Q3 earnings miss

headline: DoorDash reports more orders than expected in third quarter, but warns of higher expenses ahead
summary: DoorDash reported higher-than-expected orders and revenue in the third quarter but warned investors that it will be spending significantly more on product development next year.  The San Francisco-based delivery company said Wednesday its total orders rose 21% to 776 million in the July-September period.  DoorDash said its revenue jumped 27% to $3.45 billion.

headline: DoorDash (NASDAQ:DASH) Posts Better-Than-Expected Sales In Q3 But Stock Drops 16.8%
summary: On-demand food delivery service DoorDash (NYSE:DASH) reported revenue ahead of Wall Streets expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 27.3% year on year to $3.45 billion. Its GAAP profit of $0.55 per share was 18.7% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
